Vice President Biden delivers a speech at the welcome home ceremony for the 2nd Brigade Combat Team from Iraq at Fort Drum, New York. He thanks the soldiers for their service and welcomes them home. He acknowledges the sacrifices made by military families and expresses gratitude for their support. He highlights the achievements of the 10th Mountain Division and the success of the mission in Iraq. He discusses the upcoming end of the combat mission in Iraq and the transition to a civilian-led effort. He emphasizes the importance of a stable Iraq for the region and the role of the Iraqi people in shaping their own future. He praises the accomplishments of the soldiers and expresses condolences for those who have lost their lives. He discusses the government's commitment to supporting military families and caring for wounded warriors. He concludes by recognizing the dawn of a new era in Iraq and the bravery of the American soldiers.